Create both `MutablePoint` (fields changeable via setters) and `ImmutablePoint` (all fields final, no setters, `withX(int x)` returns a new instance).

**MutablePoint example:**
MutablePoint p = new MutablePoint(1,2);
p.setX(10);
p.getX() => 10

**ImmutablePoint example:**
