problems.description:
Implement the **Prototype pattern**: a `Shape` interface with `clone()` method, implemented by `Circle(double radius)` and `Rectangle(double width, double height)`. `clone()` must return a deep copy.

**Example:**
Circle c1 = new Circle(5.0);
Circle c2 = (Circle) c1.clone();
c2.setRadius(10.0);
c1.getRadius() => 5.0   // original unchanged
c2.getRadius() => 10.0

**Key insight:** Prototype avoids expensive re-initialization — clone an existing object instead of constructing from scratch. Deep copy ensures independence.

problems.starterCode:
import java.util.*;

public class ShapeRegistry {
    abstract static class Shape {
        String color;
        Shape(String color) { this.color = color; }
        abstract Shape clone();
        abstract double area();
    }

    static class Circle extends Shape {
        double radius;
        Circle(double radius, String color) { super(color); this.radius = radius; }
        // TODO: clone()
        @Override public double area() { return Math.PI * radius * radius; }
        @Override public String toString() { return "Circle r=" + radius + " col=" + color; }
    }

    static class Rectangle extends Shape {
        double w, h;
        Rectangle(double w, double h, String color) { super(color); this.w=w; this.h=h; }
        // TODO: clone()
        @Override public double area() { return w * h; }
        @Override public String toString() { return "Rect " + w + "x" + h + " col=" + color; }
    }

    private Map<String, Shape> prototypes = new HashMap<>();
    public void register(String name, Shape s) { prototypes.put(name, s); }
    public Shape create(String name) { return prototypes.get(name).clone(); }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ShapeRegistry reg = new ShapeRegistry();
        reg.register("smallCircle", new Circle(5, "red"));
        reg.register("bigRect",     new Rectangle(10, 20, "blue"));

        Shape c1 = reg.create("smallCircle");
        Shape c2 = reg.create("smallCircle");
        System.out.println(c1);        // Circle r=5.0 col=red
        System.out.println(c1 == c2);  // false — different objects!
        c1.color = "green";            // mutating copy doesn't affect prototype
        System.out.println(reg.create("smallCircle").color); // red
    }
}

